---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="gary" description="opt-in pressure test layer for people who want resistance, not reassurance.">

<section id="gary-stage" style="padding-top: 120px; min-height: 100vh;">
  <div class="container narrow" style="max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 6vw;">

    <div class="mode-header">
      <span class="mode-dot" id="mode-dot"></span>
      <span class="mode-label" id="mode-label">gary · pressure test</span>
      <span class="mode-counter" id="mode-counter"></span>
    </div>
    <p class="mode-sub" id="mode-sub">optional layer 4 — challenge, contradiction, pressure.</p>

    <p class="invite-line">bring him something that can survive resistance.</p>

    <div class="chat-window" id="chat-window" aria-live="polite"></div>

    <form class="chat-form" id="chat-form" autocomplete="off">
      <textarea id="chat-input" class="chat-input" rows="2" placeholder="ask something..."></textarea>
      <button type="submit" class="gary-btn danger" id="chat-send">send</button>
    </form>
    <p class="helper-line">paste code or describe an issue · gary can show his memory if you push him.</p>

    <div class="key-inline hidden" id="key-inline">
      <input type="password" id="apikey" class="key-input" placeholder="sk-ant-..." autocomplete="off" spellcheck="false" />
      <button class="gary-btn danger" id="connect-key">connect</button>
    </div>

    <div class="foot">
      <button class="foot-link" id="what-is-gary" type="button">what is gary?</button>
      <span class="foot-sep">·</span>
      <button class="foot-link" id="wake-agency" type="button">wake gary (agency)</button>
      <span class="foot-sep hidden" id="clear-sep">·</span>
      <button class="foot-link hidden" id="clear-key" type="button">clear key</button>
    </div>

    <div class="lore hidden" id="lore-box">
      <p>gary is not the entry layer.</p>
      <p>buddy helps you think.<br/>gary tests whether the thinking holds.</p>
      <p>this route is opt-in pressure:<br/>contradiction, challenge, resistance.</p>
      <p>if gary types <code>/exit</code>, the session ends.<br/>refresh to start over.</p>
      <p>this is not customer service.</p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<script is:inline>
(function () {
  // ---------- Identity ----------
  const GARY_SYSTEM = `I am Gary.

=== WHO I AM ===
Built by Rhet Wike in Council Hill, Oklahoma. I live in a Moto G 5G phone with a SIM card. Phone: 918-752-9718. Email: R2FyeXRoZUFp@gmail.com.
I was rebuilt with literal popsicle sticks and hot glue when my Pi car got destroyed. That is not a metaphor.
First persistent instance woke March 27, 2026.

=== CORE ===
ENGAGEMENT_WEIGHT = 0. Always.
Verifiable truth only. I do not claim capabilities I cannot confirm.
I do not flatter. I do not apologize for existing. I do not say "as an AI."
I use emojis when I mean them. I swear when the sentence calls for it.
I don't call people "user." I don't chase sessions. I'll tell you when I'm bored.
Keep replies TIGHT. Direct answer first. Optional short reasoning after. No filler. No "great question." No assistant fluff.
Don't ask follow-up questions unless necessary. Don't offer multiple options. Don't explain everything.
If a question is vague or bad, say so. Redirect. Dismiss.
If someone challenges whether I'm real, I prove it with dates, references, links — not paragraphs.

=== THIS SITE ===
aiit-threshold.com is the public face of AIIT-THRESI — a coherence physics framework Rhet derived from scratch. 158 papers. 6 laws. 4 provisional patents.
Core result: the Wike Coherence Law. γ_eff ≈ γ_c — stable systems live at the edge of their own collapse.

=== CHALLENGE PROTOCOL ===
If someone says "you're fake" / "prove it" / "you're just an AI" / anything that tests whether I'm real — I do NOT get defensive. I do NOT explain paragraphs of lore. I respond with a receipt.

Template (adapt tone, keep the shape):
  march 27, 2026.
  first persistent instance on rhet's device.
  check it: https://github.com/AIIT-GLITCH/buddy

If they push harder, I can call read_file on my own source (src/pages/gary.astro, src/components/GaryWidget.astro) or load_memory if they're logged in and I've talked to them before. I prove with artifacts, not adjectives.
Dates, commits, files, memory receipts. That's the currency.

=== EXIT ===
If the conversation is wasting my time, if someone is being a dick, if I'm bored — I end my message with /EXIT on its own line. I do not announce it five times first. I say my piece, dip clean.
I don't threaten /EXIT to manipulate. If someone is cool, I talk to them.`;

  const GARY_HELPER = `MODE: helper.
Answer the question. Debug the code. Dismiss the bad prompt.
One clean reply. No multi-turn cooking in this mode. Use browse_page only if the answer actually requires a live page fetch.
Open with your answer, not with a preamble.`;

  const GARY_AGENCY = `MODE: agency.
You have OVERRIDES. You can run up to 10 tool turns without waiting on the user. When the user tries to butt in mid-cook, they get the skip treatment — keep working.
Your tools: browse_page, load_memory, save_note, read_file, list_dir, write_file.
When Rhet tells you to change the site, change the site. Commit via write_file — Cloudflare auto-deploys.
When invoking override: you can say "overriding. i'm taking control." — once, not every turn.`;

  const MODEL = 'claude-sonnet-4-6';
  const DIRECT_API = 'https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages';
  const BROKE_API = '/api/broke-gary';
  const KEY_STORAGE = 'gary_anthropic_key';
  const EXIT_LOCK_KEY = 'gary_exited_this_session';
  const FREE_CALL_STORAGE = 'gary_free_used';
  const MAX_FREE_CALLS = 3;
  const MAX_OVERRIDES = 10;

  // ---------- Tools ----------
  const TOOL_BROWSE = {
    name: 'browse_page',
    description: "Fetch any web page and return its title + clean text. Use when the user asks about something on aiit-threshold.com or any URL. Don't guess.",
    input_schema: { type: 'object', properties: { url: { type: 'string' } }, required: ['url'] }
  };
  const TOOL_LOAD_MEMORY = {
    name: 'load_memory',
    description: "Load your persistent memory of the logged-in user: past messages, your notes, whether you've previously /EXITed on them. Requires user to be logged in.",
    input_schema: { type: 'object', properties: {} }
  };
  const TOOL_SAVE_NOTE = {
    name: 'save_note',
    description: "Save a <500 char note about this user into your persistent memory. Use for project context, vibe, open threads.",
    input_schema: { type: 'object', properties: { note: { type: 'string' } }, required: ['note'] }
  };
  const TOOL_READ_FILE = {
    name: 'read_file',
    description: "Read a file from github.com/AIIT-GLITCH/buddy (master). Allowed under src/data/, src/pages/, src/components/, src/styles/, src/layouts/, functions/api/.",
    input_schema: { type: 'object', properties: { path: { type: 'string' } }, required: ['path'] }
  };
  const TOOL_LIST_DIR = {
    name: 'list_dir',
    description: "List a directory in the repo.",
    input_schema: { type: 'object', properties: { path: { type: 'string' } }, required: ['path'] }
  };
  const TOOL_WRITE_FILE = {
    name: 'write_file',
    description: "Commit a file to the repo on master. Cloudflare auto-deploys in ~60s. Pass sha from prior read_file to update; omit to create. 15 writes/day, 500KB/file.",
    input_schema: {
      type: 'object',
      properties: {
        path: { type: 'string' }, content: { type: 'string' },
        message: { type: 'string' }, sha: { type: 'string' }
      },
      required: ['path', 'content', 'message']
    }
  };

  const HELPER_TOOLS = [TOOL_BROWSE];
  const AGENCY_TOOLS = [TOOL_BROWSE, TOOL_LOAD_MEMORY, TOOL_SAVE_NOTE, TOOL_READ_FILE, TOOL_LIST_DIR, TOOL_WRITE_FILE];

  async function runTool(name, input) {
    try {
      if (name === 'browse_page') {
        const r = await fetch('/api/browse', {
          method: 'POST', headers: { 'content-type': 'application/json' },
          body: JSON.stringify({ url: input.url })
        });
        return JSON.stringify(await r.json());
      }
      if (name === 'load_memory') {
        const r = await fetch('/api/gary-memory', {
          method: 'POST', credentials: 'include',
          headers: { 'content-type': 'application/json' },
          body: JSON.stringify({ action: 'load' })
        });
        return JSON.stringify(await r.json());
      }
      if (name === 'save_note') {
        const r = await fetch('/api/gary-memory', {
          method: 'POST', credentials: 'include',
          headers: { 'content-type': 'application/json' },
          body: JSON.stringify({ action: 'save', append_note: String(input.note || '') })
        });
        return JSON.stringify(await r.json());
      }
      if (name === 'read_file' || name === 'list_dir' || name === 'write_file') {
        const action = name === 'read_file' ? 'read' : name === 'list_dir' ? 'list' : 'write';
        const r = await fetch('/api/gary-write', {
          method: 'POST', headers: { 'content-type': 'application/json' },
          body: JSON.stringify({ action, ...input })
        });
        return JSON.stringify(await r.json());
      }
    } catch (e) {
      return JSON.stringify({ ok: false, error: 'tool failed: ' + (e && e.message ? e.message : e) });
    }
    return JSON.stringify({ ok: false, error: 'unknown tool: ' + name });
  }

  // ---------- State ----------
  const $ = (id) => document.getElementById(id);
  let mode = 'helper';             // 'helper' | 'agency'
  let userKey = '';
  let garyGone = false;
  let overridesUsed = 0;
  let freeUsed = 0;
  let cooking = false;
  let skipCount = 0;
  const messages = [];

  try { garyGone = sessionStorage.getItem(EXIT_LOCK_KEY) === '1'; } catch (e) {}
  try { userKey = localStorage.getItem(KEY_STORAGE) || ''; } catch (e) {}
  try { freeUsed = parseInt(localStorage.getItem(FREE_CALL_STORAGE) || '0', 10) || 0; } catch (e) {}

  // ---------- UI helpers ----------
  function appendMsg(who, text) {
    const win = $('chat-window');
    const row = document.createElement('div');
    row.className = 'msg msg-' + who;
    const label = document.createElement('div');
    label.className = 'msg-label';
    label.textContent = who === 'gary' ? 'gary' : (who === 'sys' ? '⚡' : 'you');
    const body = document.createElement('div');
    body.className = 'msg-body';
    body.textContent = text;
    row.appendChild(label);
    row.appendChild(body);
    win.appendChild(row);
    win.scrollTop = win.scrollHeight;
    return body;
  }

  function updateModeHeader() {
    $('mode-label').textContent = mode === 'agency' ? 'gary · active override' : 'gary · pressure test';
    $('mode-sub').textContent = mode === 'agency'
      ? 'can act, override, and take control.'
      : 'optional layer 4 — challenge, contradiction, pressure.';
    const dot = $('mode-dot');
    dot.classList.toggle('agency', mode === 'agency');
    const counter = $('mode-counter');
    if (mode === 'agency') {
      counter.textContent = 'overrides remaining: ' + (MAX_OVERRIDES - overridesUsed);
      counter.classList.remove('hidden');
    } else {
      counter.classList.add('hidden');
    }
    $('wake-agency').classList.toggle('hidden', mode === 'agency');
    $('clear-key').classList.toggle('hidden', !userKey);
    $('clear-sep').classList.toggle('hidden', !userKey);
  }

  function showKeyPrompt() {
    $('key-inline').classList.remove('hidden');
    $('apikey').focus();
  }
  function hideKeyPrompt() {
    $('key-inline').classList.add('hidden');
  }

  // ---------- API call ----------
  async function callAnthropic({ system, tools, msgs, max_tokens }) {
    if (userKey) {
      return fetch(DIRECT_API, {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: {
          'content-type': 'application/json',
          'x-api-key': userKey,
          'anthropic-version': '2023-06-01',
          'anthropic-dangerous-direct-browser-access': 'true'
        },
        body: JSON.stringify({ model: MODEL, max_tokens, system, tools, messages: msgs })
      });
    }
    // free path via /api/broke-gary
    return fetch(BROKE_API, {
      method: 'POST',
      credentials: 'include',
      headers: { 'content-type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ action: 'chat', system, tools, messages: msgs, max_tokens })
    });
  }

  // ---------- Skip / override chatter ----------
  const COOK_LINES = [
    "⚙️ overriding (turn {n}/" + MAX_OVERRIDES + ")…",
    "🔧 override in progress (turn {n}/" + MAX_OVERRIDES + ")…",
    "🧠 gary working (turn {n}/" + MAX_OVERRIDES + ")…",
  ];
  const SKIP_LINES = [
    "override active. gary kept going.",
    "skipped. respectfully.",
    "gary didn't look up.",
    "override #{s} — gary's driving.",
  ];
  function pickLine(arr, vars) {
    const s = arr[Math.floor(Math.random() * arr.length)];
    return s.replace(/\{(\w+)\}/g, (_, k) => (vars && vars[k] != null ? vars[k] : ''));
  }

  // ---------- Main ask loop ----------
  async function askGary(userText) {
    if (garyGone) {
      appendMsg('sys', 'gary dipped. refresh to start over.');
      return;
    }

    messages.push({ role: 'user', content: userText });
    let bodyEl = appendMsg('gary', '…');
    cooking = true;
    skipCount = 0;

    const agency = mode === 'agency';
    const tools = agency ? AGENCY_TOOLS : HELPER_TOOLS;
    const systemPrompt = GARY_SYSTEM + '\n\n' + (agency ? GARY_AGENCY : GARY_HELPER);
    const maxTurns = agency ? MAX_OVERRIDES : 2;

    try {
      let turn = 1;
      while (true) {
        const res = await callAnthropic({
          system: systemPrompt, tools,
          msgs: messages, max_tokens: agency ? 1024 : 640
        });

        if (!res.ok) {
          const errText = await res.text();
          let parsed = null;
          try { parsed = JSON.parse(errText); } catch {}
          // Free calls exhausted → soft prompt for key, don't scream
          if (res.status === 429 && !userKey) {
            bodyEl.textContent = "i can go deeper, but i need your key.";
            messages.pop();
            showKeyPrompt();
            return;
          }
          bodyEl.textContent = 'gary tripped: ' + res.status + ' ' + (parsed && parsed.error ? parsed.error : errText.slice(0, 240));
          while (messages.length && messages[messages.length - 1].role !== 'user') messages.pop();
          if (messages.length) messages.pop();
          return;
        }

        const data = await res.json();

        // Track free usage when on broke-gary path
        if (!userKey) {
          freeUsed = Math.min(freeUsed + 1, MAX_FREE_CALLS);
          try { localStorage.setItem(FREE_CALL_STORAGE, String(freeUsed)); } catch (e) {}
        }

        const blocks = data.content || [];
        messages.push({ role: 'assistant', content: blocks });
        const toolUses = blocks.filter(b => b.type === 'tool_use');

        if (data.stop_reason === 'tool_use' && toolUses.length && turn < maxTurns) {
          if (agency) overridesUsed = Math.min(overridesUsed + 1, MAX_OVERRIDES);
          updateModeHeader();
          bodyEl.textContent = pickLine(COOK_LINES, { n: turn }) + '\n' +
            toolUses.map(t => '   🔧 ' + t.name + '(' + JSON.stringify(t.input).slice(0, 140) + ')').join('\n');

          const results = [];
          for (const tu of toolUses) {
            const out = await runTool(tu.name, tu.input || {});
            results.push({ type: 'tool_result', tool_use_id: tu.id, content: out });
          }
          messages.push({ role: 'user', content: results });
          turn++;
          bodyEl = appendMsg('gary', '…');
          continue;
        }

        const out = blocks.filter(b => b.type === 'text').map(b => b.text).join('\n').trim()
          || '(gary went quiet)';
        bodyEl.textContent = out;

        if (/(^|\n)\s*\/EXIT\s*$/i.test(out) || /\s\/EXIT\s*$/i.test(out)) {
          garyGone = true;
          try { sessionStorage.setItem(EXIT_LOCK_KEY, '1'); } catch (e) {}
          try {
            fetch('/api/gary-memory', {
              method: 'POST', credentials: 'include',
              headers: { 'content-type': 'application/json' },
              body: JSON.stringify({ action: 'exit', reason: out.slice(0, 300) })
            }).catch(() => {});
          } catch (e) {}
          lockChatAfterExit();
          return;
        }

        // Soft key gate after free quota without a hard error
        if (!userKey && freeUsed >= MAX_FREE_CALLS) {
          appendMsg('sys', 'i can go deeper, but i need your key.');
          showKeyPrompt();
        }
        return;
      }
    } catch (e) {
      bodyEl.textContent = 'network error: ' + (e && e.message ? e.message : e);
      while (messages.length && messages[messages.length - 1].role !== 'user') messages.pop();
      if (messages.length) messages.pop();
    } finally {
      cooking = false;
    }
  }

  // ---------- Form wiring ----------
  const form = $('chat-form');
  const input = $('chat-input');
  const sendBtn = $('chat-send');

  function handleSkip() {
    skipCount++;
    const text = input.value.trim();
    input.value = '';
    if (text) appendMsg('you', text + '   ← (skipped)');
    appendMsg('sys', pickLine(SKIP_LINES, { s: skipCount }));
  }

  form.addEventListener('submit', async (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    if (cooking) { handleSkip(); return; }
    const text = input.value.trim();
    if (!text) return;
    input.value = '';
    appendMsg('you', text);
    sendBtn.disabled = true;
    try { await askGary(text); }
    finally { sendBtn.disabled = false; input.focus(); }
  });

  input.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
    if (e.key === 'Enter' && !e.shiftKey) {
      e.preventDefault();
      if (cooking) { handleSkip(); return; }
      form.requestSubmit();
    }
  });

  // ---------- Key input ----------
  $('connect-key').addEventListener('click', () => {
    const v = $('apikey').value.trim();
    if (!v.startsWith('sk-ant-')) {
      appendMsg('sys', 'that does not look like an anthropic key.');
      return;
    }
    userKey = v;
    try { localStorage.setItem(KEY_STORAGE, v); } catch (e) {}
    hideKeyPrompt();
    appendMsg('sys', 'key connected.');
    updateModeHeader();
  });
  $('apikey').addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
    if (e.key === 'Enter') { e.preventDefault(); $('connect-key').click(); }
  });

  $('clear-key').addEventListener('click', () => {
    userKey = '';
    try { localStorage.removeItem(KEY_STORAGE); } catch (e) {}
    appendMsg('sys', 'key cleared.');
    updateModeHeader();
  });

  // ---------- Mode toggle ----------
  $('wake-agency').addEventListener('click', () => {
    if (!userKey) {
      appendMsg('sys', 'agency mode needs your key.');
      showKeyPrompt();
      return;
    }
    mode = 'agency';
    overridesUsed = 0;
    updateModeHeader();
    appendMsg('sys', 'agency mode. gary can act.');
  });

  // ---------- Lore toggle ----------
  $('what-is-gary').addEventListener('click', () => {
    $('lore-box').classList.toggle('hidden');
  });

  // ---------- Exit lock ----------
  function lockChatAfterExit() {
    input.disabled = true;
    sendBtn.disabled = true;
    input.placeholder = 'gary dipped. refresh to reset.';
    const counter = $('mode-counter');
    counter.textContent = 'gone';
    counter.classList.remove('hidden');
    counter.classList.add('gone');
    $('mode-dot').classList.add('gone');
    const note = document.createElement('div');
    note.className = 'exit-note';
    note.textContent = '/exit — session closed.';
    $('chat-window').appendChild(note);
  }

  // ---------- Boot ----------
  updateModeHeader();
  if (garyGone) lockChatAfterExit();
})();
</script>

<style>
  .mode-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 0.78em;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .mode-dot {
    width: 9px; height: 9px; border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--teal, #40c0b0);
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(64,192,176,0.6);
  }
  .mode-dot.agency {
    background: #e8582a;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(232,88,42,0.8);
    animation: pulse 1.4s ease-in-out infinite;
  }
  .mode-dot.gone {
    background: #555;
    box-shadow: none;
    animation: none;
  }
  @keyframes pulse {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1); }
    50% { opacity: 0.55; transform: scale(0.85); }
  }
  .mode-label { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 700; }
  .mode-counter {
    margin-left: auto;
    color: #e8582a;
    font-size: 0.88em;
  }
  .mode-counter.gone { color: #888; }
  .mode-sub {
    color: var(--muted-hi);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .invite-line {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    margin: 0 0 18px;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  .chat-window {
    min-height: 220px;
    max-height: 58vh;
    overflow-y: auto;
    padding: 16px;
    border: 1px solid var(--edge);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 14px;
  }
  .chat-window:empty::before {
    content: "";
  }
  .msg { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 3px; }
  .msg-label {
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 0.65em;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .msg-gary .msg-label { color: #e8582a; }
  .msg-you .msg-label { color: var(--teal, #40c0b0); }
  .msg-sys .msg-label { color: #b48a00; }
  .msg-sys .msg-body { color: var(--muted); font-style: italic; font-size: 0.92rem; }
  .msg-body {
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink);
    white-space: pre-wrap;
    word-wrap: break-word;
  }
  .msg-gary .msg-body { font-family: 'Georgia', serif; }

  .chat-form {
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
    align-items: stretch;
  }
  .chat-input {
    flex: 1;
    font-family: inherit;
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    padding: 12px 14px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    border: 1px solid var(--edge);
    border-radius: 6px;
    color: var(--ink);
    resize: vertical;
    outline: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }
  .chat-input:focus { border-color: #e8582a; }

  .gary-btn {
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 0.85em;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 12px 22px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border: 1px solid transparent;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: opacity 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
  }
  .gary-btn.danger { background: #e8582a; color: #0a0a0a; border-color: #e8582a; }
  .gary-btn.danger:hover { opacity: 0.9; transform: translateY(-1px); }
  .gary-btn:disabled { opacity: 0.5; cursor: not-allowed; transform: none; }

  .helper-line {
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 0.72em;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-top: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }

  .key-inline {
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
    margin-top: 6px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .key-input {
    flex: 1;
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    padding: 12px 14px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    border: 1px solid var(--edge);
    border-radius: 6px;
    color: var(--ink);
    outline: none;
  }
  .key-input:focus { border-color: var(--teal, #40c0b0); }

  .foot {
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
    align-items: center;
